                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/968: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-14T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 14, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 14—11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. My telegram No. 441, October 5, 11 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d601fn30">Not
                        printed.</note> By note dated October 10th received today the Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs formally advises that “the Government of His Majesty the King of
                    Italy and of Albania, Emperor of Ethiopia has on its part decided to avail
                    itself of the option contemplated by article 24 paragraph 2 of naval treaty and
                    declares the operation thereof to be suspended insofar as it is concerned.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
